article.headline: Portland 72, Lewis &amp, Clark 49
article.story: PORTLAND, Ore. -- Robin Smeulders scored 12 points as Portland pulled away down the stretch for a 72-49 victory over Lewis & Clark College in a non-conference game Tuesday night that ended the regular season. T.J. Campbell and Luke Sikma each added 10 points for the Pilots (20-9), who will enter this weekend's West Coast Conference tournament as the No. 3 seed. Lewis & Clark's Josh Kollasch led all scorers with 15 points as the Pioneers slipped to 10-16.
